[2025-01-12 21:44:51] USER: how are meanders formed
[2025-01-12 21:44:54] ASSISTANT: Meanders are formed through the natural process of erosion and deposition in a river. As water flows in a river, it erodes the outer banks and deposits sediment on the inner banks. This process is influenced by the speed and volume of the water, as well as the type of sediment present. Over time, these actions cause the river to develop a winding, snake-like pattern known as meanders. The continuous erosion and deposition accentuate the bends, making them more pronounced.
